X = np.array(data['Horsepower'], dtype=float)

for i in range(n_degrees):
    c = np.polyfit(X, Y, degrees[i])
    Y_model = model(X, c)
    BIC_degree[i] = bic(Y, Y_model, p=degrees[i])

plt.plot(degrees, BIC_degree)
plt.xlabel("degree")
plt.ylabel("Bayesian Information Criterion")
